------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Release notes for Agda 2 version 2.2.4
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Important changes since 2.2.2:

* Change to open import and open module semantics
  
    open import M <using/hiding/renaming>

  now translates to

    import A
    open A <using/hiding/renaming>

  instead of

    import A <using/hiding/renaming>
    open A

  The same translation is used for "open module M = E ..."

  This means that import directives does not affect the qualified names when
  using open import/module. To get the old behaviour simply use the expanded
  version above.

* Public open in parameterised modules no longer inherit the module
  parameters. Example:

    module A where
      postulate X : Set

    module B (Y : Set) where
      open A public

    -- Agda-2.2.2   B.X : (Y : Set) -> Set
    -- Agda-2.2.4   B.X : Set

